    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:41
    old "I am Maanai, High Priestess of the Great Temple of Zeta, this is my wisdom.\n\nAs servants of the Temple, the Priestesses that I lead must serve the Gods, the Queen and the City, in that order, but all too often, I see young girls seeking to join the Temple's servants more for the free meals and the security that the position offers. Do they believe in the Queen? Do they want to serve the Gods? Do they make the choice out of a sense of civic duty to the City? Or has this really become a refuge for destitute women? Any one of the three reasons would suffice, but often it is not the case. It pains me, when it happens, to have to relegate to the slave pens those young girls who ask to join purely out of desperation, to escape slavery, destitution, or an unhappy union... but it must be done.\n\nThe missions of preaching the faith of the Gods, of bringing hope and spiritual comfort to the ill, the weak and the downcast is a sacred duty, that should not be handed to those that don't believe. The mission of bolstering the population of Zeta should be given to those who are strong in body, mind and spirit, and who believe in something greater than themselves, whether it's the Gods, their representative the Queen, or the duty to serve the sacred City of Zeta. How else but by following an ideal greater than oneself, can a woman accept to bring to term multiple pregnancies only to renounce the fruits of their womb time and time again, when they are weaned off the mother's milk? The heartache would be too much to bear if not supported by faith in something.\n\nFor this reason, I hereby decree that the full rank of Priestess of the Temple will only be attained after an extended period of thirty years of service as a Vessel for the Children of Zeta. Those women who do not complete the full term of thirty years, will have failed the City, The Gods and the Temple, and will therefore be banished into slavery.\n\nThe idea of serving for such a long time to produce citizens, soldiers, men and women of Zeta, should scare away those girls who think to use the Temple as an easy way out of the dangers and hardships of life in this desert land. During their years of service as Vessels, the chosen ones will live in the Temple and be well cared for. After a pregnancy should come full term, suitable matches will be arranged as soon as it is viable for them to produce another Child of Zeta. Once their thirty years of service in this fashion have come to pass, they will ascend to the rank of full Priestess, return to the world, or stay on as servants to the Temple, depending on their choice. The Children of Zeta they will bear will be given to deserving and suitable families to raise and become productive members of Zetan society, or educated to serve as guards, soldiers, bureaucrats to the Temple, to the Palace and to the City of Zeta in general.\n\nDuring their thirty years of service, these women will be known as Vessels or by the generic title of Priestess, and the use of their given names will be forbidden to them and to those that address them. Nameless and bound in servitude to the Temple, the public shall address them with the honorific of Revered Mothers only, for they will be like mothers to all of Zeta. Their birth names will be recorded in the Temple ledgers and will be restored to them upon the successful completion of their service as Vessels.\n\nThis I decree for the good of the Temple and of all of Zeta, with the blessing and the authority of the Queen.\n\nHeed my words,\n\nI am Maanai, High Priestess."
    new "Soy Maanai, Suma Sacerdotisa del Gran Templo de Zeta, esta es mi sabiduría.\n\nComo servidoras del Templo, las Sacerdotisas que lidero deben servir a los Dioses, a la Reina y a la Ciudad, en ese orden, pero con demasiada frecuencia veo a jóvenes que buscan unirse a las servidoras del Templo más por las comidas gratuitas y la seguridad que ofrece el puesto. ¿Creen en la Reina? ¿Quieren servir a los Dioses? ¿Toman la decisión por un sentido de deber cívico hacia la Ciudad? ¿O se ha convertido realmente esto en un refugio para mujeres desamparadas? Cualquiera de las tres razones sería suficiente, pero a menudo no es el caso. Me duele, cuando sucede, tener que relegar a los corrales de esclavos a esas jóvenes que piden unirse puramente por desesperación, para escape de la esclavitud, la indigencia o una unión infeliz... pero debe hacerse.\n\nLas misiones de predicar la fe en los Dioses, de llevar esperanza y consuelo espiritual a los enfermos, los débiles y los abatidos es un deber sagrado que no debe entregarse a quienes no creen. La misión de reforzar la población de Zeta debe encomendarse a quienes son fuertes de cuerpo, mente y espíritu, y que creen en algo más grande que ellos mismos, ya sean los Dioses, su representante la Reina, o el deber de servir a la sagrada Ciudad de Zeta. ¿De qué otro modo, si no es siguiendo un ideal más grande que uno mismo, puede una mujer aceptar llevar a término múltiples embarazos solo para renunciar una y otra vez a los frutos de su vientre cuando son destetados de la leche materna? La angustia sería demasiado grande de soportar si no estuviera apoyada por la fe en algo.\n\nPor esta razón, por la presente decreto que el rango completo de Sacerdotisa del Templo solo se alcanzará después de un largo período de treinta años de servicio como Vasija para los Hijos de Zeta. Aquellas mujeres que no completen el período completo de treinta años habrán fallado a la Ciudad, a los Dioses y al Templo, y por lo tanto serán desterradas a la esclavitud.\n\nLa idea de servir durante tanto tiempo para producir ciudadanos, soldados, hombres y mujeres de Zeta debería ahuyentar a aquellas muchachas que piensan en usar el Templo como una salida fácil de los peligros y las dificultades de la vida en esta tierra desértica. Durante sus años de servicio como Vasijas, las elegidas vivirán en el Templo y serán bien cuidadas. Después de que un embarazo llegue a término, se concertarán uniones adecuadas tan pronto como sea viable para que puedan producir otro Hijo de Zeta. Una vez que sus treinta años de servicio de esta manera hayan pasado, ascenderán al rango de Sacerdotisa plena, regresarán al mundo o permanecerán como servidoras del Templo, según su elección. Los Hijos de Zeta que den a luz serán entregados a familias merecedoras y adecuadas para que los críen y se conviertan en miembros productivos de la sociedad zetana, o serán educados para servir como guardias, soldados, burócratas del Templo, del Palacio y de la Ciudad de Zeta en general.\n\nDurante sus treinta años de servicio, estas mujeres serán conocidas como Vasijas o por el título genérico de Sacerdotisa, y se les prohibirá el uso de sus nombres de pila, tanto a ellas como a quienes se dirijan a ellas. Sin nombre y atadas en servidumbre al Templo, el público se dirigirá a ellas solo con el honorífico de Madres Veneradas, pues serán como madres para todo Zeta. Sus nombres de nacimiento se registrarán en los libros del Templo y se les devolverán al completar con éxito su servicio como Vasijas.\n\nEsto lo decreto por el bien del Templo y de todo Zeta, con la bendición y la autoridad de la Reina.\n\nEscuchad mis palabras,\n\nSoy Maanai, Suma Sacerdotisa."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:76
    old "Might Makes Right"
    new "El Poder es la Ley"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:76
    old "{i}The parchment is dry but still soft to the touch, with care, it can be unfolded. It's easily a few centuries old, but the writing is still clear.{/i}\n\nI am Aker, the third of my name. Hear my wisdom and heed my words.\n\nSince the End of Days, men and women have fought tooth and nail over the scraps of what is left of society. The adage goes that Might makes Right. It's not entirely true, nor is it that simple once you move in polite company, amongst your peers or even your betters; but at its core, this is what our society today is built upon.\n\nStrength of body and character have become the deciding factor to determine status and, quite often, survival. You take what you want, within reason and your own judgement, and you keep what you can.\n\nLet me, however, give you further advice on how to conduct your life profitably, with honour and strength. Beware of the weak who band together, for they may still defeat you. Be kind to those beneath you, for the debts of gratitude and sincere affection are bonds more powerful than steel. Be true to your word whenever you can; your reputation might be the only thing protecting you from a knife in the back. Do not shy away from opportunity; boldness without brashness is the mark of a leader of men. Be generous with what you have; a display of status can be a statement as strong as flexing your physical prowess. However, do not flaunt your wealth, such as it is. You don't want to place a target on your House, and there is a reason peacocks only survive in depictions on ancient tombs.\n\nThis is my wisdom, Aker, third of my name. Desert Stalker.\n\nD 27, Y 103 since the Founding of Zeta"
    new "{i}El pergamino está seco pero sigue siendo suave al tacto; con cuidado, se puede desplegar.{/i}\n\nSoy Aker, el tercero de mi nombre. Escucha mi sabiduría y presta atención a mis palabras.\n\nDesde el Fin de los Días, hombres y mujeres han luchado con uñas y dientes por los restos de lo que queda de la sociedad. El adagio dice que el Poder hace el Derecho. No es del todo cierto, ni es tan sencillo una vez que te mueves en compañía educada, entre tus iguales o incluso tus superiores; pero en el fondo, esto es sobre lo que se construye nuestra sociedad actual.\n\nLa fuerza del cuerpo y el carácter se han convertido en el factor decisivo para determinar el estatus y, muy a menudo, la supervivencia. Coges lo que quieres, dentro de lo razonable y de tu propio juicio, y te quedas con lo que puedes.\n\nPermíteme, sin embargo, darte más consejos sobre cómo llevar tu vida de forma provechosa, con honor y fuerza. Ten cuidado con los débiles que se unen, pues aún pueden derrotarte. Sé amable con los que están por debajo de ti, pues las deudas de gratitud y el afecto sincero son vínculos más poderosos que el acero. Sé fiel a tu palabra siempre que puedas; tu reputación puede ser lo único que te proteja de un puñal por la espalda. No rehúyas las oportunidades; la audacia sin descaro es la marca de un líder de hombres. Sé generoso con lo que tienes; una exhibición de estatus puede ser una declaración tan fuerte como hacer gala de tu destreza física. Sin embargo, no hagas alarde de tu riqueza. No querrás poner una diana en tu Casa, y hay una razón por la que los pavos reales sólo sobreviven en representaciones de tumbas antiguas.\n\nEsta es mi sabiduría, Aker, el tercero de mi nombre. Acechador del Desierto\n\nD 27, Y 103 desde la Fundación de Zeta."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:106
    old "The Long Walk"
    new "La Larga Marcha"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:106
    old "Being a Desert Stalker is a calling and a curse. Very few of us are successful enough to be able to retire and live a long life off the profits of our labour.  More often than not, our repeated incursions in the Zones put us at risk of contamination and of catching something that will kill us before our time, whether it's a knife cut, an illness or a mummy bite. So when our bones start to become heavy and we see the world move faster than us, do we stay on our path and go on with our lives until we can no more, or do we take the Long Walk?\n\nSome of us prefer the latter. They walk into the desert, armed with their trusted weapon, leaving everything else behind. They face the enemies they've made in their Stalker days with their heads held high. Stories tell of Stalkers being ambushed by old enemies, some who have been found lying under a palm tree, killed by exhaustion and dehydration; others still who found the room of wishes on their last journey to a Zone. When my time comes, I do not know if I will face the Long Walk or not.\n\nDo I stay with my loved ones for as long as I can and allow them to see me decay into infirmity, or do I abandon them to their fate and leave them with the memory of a strong leader of the house?\n\n- Personal records, D 184, Y 416 since the Founding of Zeta"
    new "Ser un Acechador del Desierto es una vocación y una maldición. Muy pocos de nosotros tenemos el suficiente éxito como para poder retirarnos y vivir una larga vida con los beneficios de nuestro trabajo.  La mayoría de las veces, nuestras repetidas incursiones en las Zonas nos ponen en riesgo de contaminación y de contraer algo que nos mate antes de tiempo, ya sea un corte de cuchillo, una enfermedad o una mordedura de momia. Así que cuando nuestros huesos empiezan a pesar y vemos que el mundo se mueve más rápido que nosotros, ¿nos quedamos en nuestro camino y seguimos con nuestra vida hasta que no podamos más, o emprendemos la Larga Marcha?\n\nAlgunos prefieren esto último. Caminan hacia el desierto, armados con su arma de confianza, dejando todo lo demás atrás. Se enfrentan a los enemigos que han hecho en sus días de Acechador con la cabeza bien alta. Se cuentan historias de Stalkers emboscados por viejos enemigos, algunos que han sido encontrados tumbados bajo una palmera, muertos por el agotamiento y la deshidratación; otros aún que encontraron la habitación de los deseos en su último viaje a una Zona. Cuando llegue mi hora, no sé si me enfrentaré a la Larga Marcha o no.\n\n¿Me quedo con mis seres queridos todo el tiempo que pueda y permito que me vean decaer en la enfermedad, o los abandono a su suerte y les dejo el recuerdo de un líder fuerte de la casa?\n\n- Registros personales, D 184, Y 416 desde la Fundación de Zeta"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:123
    old "Laws of Hospitality"
    new "Las Leyes de la Hospitalidad"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:123
    old "I am Hekal, Elder of Zeta. Hear my wisdom and heed my words.\n\nLet it be known, I speak with the blessing of Queen Merneith, as I tell you this. A man might live in a tent, a house or a palace, or find himself on the open sands and put up a fire. Such a man is the master of this abode, be it his residence or a temporary shelter. His is the right to defend his house, his campsite and his belongings, if he can, by the strength of his steel.\n\nRather than seeking battle, times may come for friends, relatives or even strangers to ask for hospitality, and it is good custom to accord it, when possible, if those who request it are trustworthy. We are but few, and the grains of sand are infinite. Whenever possible, we should seek to band together and lift one another up. It is also possible to temporarily share a roof without formally extending hospitality, be it to conduct a business transaction or to find a shelter for the night.\n\nBreaking bread together, sharing a companion or personal items of other nature signals the acceptance of the request for hospitality just as well as a spoken declaration to that effect.\n\nThe host should be generous with his possessions to make the stay comfortable and assist those guests who might find themselves in a state of need. When determining the generosity of their hospitality, a host would do well to consider the status of the guests, for it is also not proper to insult a Honoured Guests by serving them scraps from the table, and the higher the status of the guest, the more careful such considerations must be. Conversely, the guest should honour that generosity and not ask for more than is given. It is to be understood that the hosts are freely sharing what they can. A guest should not offend the master of the house, his subjects or family, nor should they offend other guests they might find under the same roof. Offending another guest is offending the master of the house.\n\nDuring such a time as one is a Honoured Guest, stealing from, or bringing violence upon the host, in words or actions, breaks the pact of hospitality. During such a time as one is a host, it is improper to steal or otherwise abuse the property and the person of the Honored Guests. This too will break the pact of hospitality. Queen Merneith shall not pass judgement upon those who take actions commensurate to repairing the insult, whether it be brought by the host or the guest. Breaking the rules of hospitality, be it in a home in Zeta or on a campsite far in the desert sands, is an insult to the Quee. Do not insult the Queen.\n\nDuring times of great calamity such as sandstorms or Cursed storms or similar, declared enemies might find themselves forced to share a shelter. In such occurrences, a truce should be in effect, lasting a full day past the ending of said necessity for shelter.\n\nThis is my wisdom and that of Queen Merneith. Hekal, Elder of Zeta. D 31, Y 244 since the Founding of Zeta"
    new "Soy Hekal, Anciano de Zeta. Escucha mi sabiduría y presta atención a mis palabras.\n\nQue se sepa, hablo con la bendición de la reina Merneith, mientras te digo esto. Un hombre puede vivir en una tienda, en una casa o en un palacio, o encontrarse en las arenas abiertas y encender un fuego. Ese hombre es el dueño de su morada, ya sea su residencia o un refugio temporal. Suyo es el derecho a defender su casa, su campamento y sus pertenencias, si puede, con la fuerza de su acero.\n\nEn lugar de buscar la batalla, puede llegar el momento en que los amigos, los parientes o incluso los desconocidos pidan hospitalidad, y es buena costumbre concederla, cuando es posible, si los que la solicitan son de confianza. Somos pocos y los granos de arena son infinitos. Siempre que sea posible, debemos tratar de unirnos y levantarnos unos a otros. También es posible compartir temporalmente un techo sin ofrecer formalmente la hospitalidad, ya sea para llevar a cabo una transacción comercial o para encontrar un refugio para la noche.\n\nPartir el pan juntos, compartir un compañero u objetos personales de otra naturaleza señala la aceptación de la solicitud de hospitalidad igual que una declaración hablada a tal efecto.\n\nEl anfitrión debe ser generoso con sus posesiones para hacer que la estancia sea cómoda y ayudar a los huéspedes que puedan encontrarse en estado de necesidad. A la hora de determinar la generosidad de su hospitalidad, el anfitrión hará bien en tener en cuenta el estatus de los invitados, pues tampoco es adecuado insultar a un invitado de honor sirviéndole sobras de la mesa, y cuanto más elevado sea el estatus del invitado, más cuidadosas deben ser estas consideraciones. A la inversa, el invitado debe honrar esa generosidad y no pedir más de lo que se le da. Debe entenderse que los anfitriones comparten libremente lo que pueden. Un invitado no debe ofender al dueño de la casa, a sus súbditos o a su familia, ni tampoco a otros invitados que pueda encontrar bajo el mismo techo. Ofender a otro huésped es ofender al dueño de la casa.\n\nDurante el tiempo en que se es Huésped de Honor, robar o ejercer violencia sobre el anfitrión, con palabras o acciones, rompe el pacto de hospitalidad. Durante el tiempo en que uno es anfitrión, es impropio robar o abusar de otro modo de la propiedad y la persona de los Huéspedes de Honor. Esto también romperá el pacto de hospitalidad. La reina Merneith no juzgará a quienes realicen acciones acordes con la reparación del insulto, ya sea por parte del anfitrión o del invitado. Romper las reglas de la hospitalidad, ya sea en un hogar en Zeta o en un campamento en las arenas del desierto, es un insulto a la Reina. No insultes a la Reina.\n\nEn tiempos de gran calamidad, como las tormentas de arena o las tormentas malditas o similares, los enemigos declarados pueden verse obligados a compartir un refugio. En tales casos, debe haber una tregua que dure un día entero después de que termine dicha necesidad de refugio.\n\nEsta es mi sabiduría y la de la Reina Merneith. Hekal, Anciano de Zeta. D 31, Y 244 desde la fundación de Zeta"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:164
    old "My rose of the desert. She has been my faithful partner for more than two decades now. Fierce, loving, wise beyond her years and intelligent, I could not ask for a better companion to lead this House with. She knows me better than myself, knows how to calm the storm in my mind, and the temper in my heart.\n\nHer body is still that of the young woman I took for a wife, and she responds to my touch as the first time I laid my fingers on her. Never jealous, but fiercely protective of her dignity and her standing, she truly is my counterpart in more ways than I can count.\n\nOur love and companionship are the columns that support the strength of our House. She understands our [persistent.da]s in ways that I cannot, and knows how to keep order in our affairs when I am not there. Woe to the man or woman who tries to hurt her. Not the biggest storm nor the greatest distance would shield them from my wrath."
    new "Mi rosa del desierto. Ha sido mi fiel compañera durante más de dos décadas. Feroz, cariñosa, sabia más allá de su edad e inteligente, no podría pedir una compañera mejor con la que dirigir esta Casa. Me conoce mejor que yo mismo, sabe cómo calmar la tormenta de mi mente y el temperamento de mi corazón.\n\nSu cuerpo sigue siendo el de la joven que tomé por esposa, y responde a mis caricias como la primera vez que puse mis dedos sobre ella. Nunca celosa, pero ferozmente protectora de su dignidad y su posición, es realmente mi homóloga en más aspectos de los que puedo contar.\n\nNuestro amor y compañía son las columnas que sostienen la fuerza de nuestra Casa. Ella comprende a nuestras [persistent.da]s de un modo que yo no puedo, y sabe cómo mantener el orden en nuestros asuntos cuando yo no estoy. Ay del hombre o la mujer que intente herirla. Ni la mayor tormenta ni la mayor distancia les protegería de mi ira."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:178
    old "My pupil, my trainee, and quite possibly, my successor, when I shall be too old to travel the path of the desert. She has been trained by myself and several other masters in Zeta to become a Desert Stalker in her own right, and the time for that to happen is fast approaching.\n\nI know there are unspoken truths and feelings that we have both pushed to the side, to concentrate on her teachings. I hope that this will not come to be something I will regret, or that might put her in danger. I hope that sacrificing our physical intimacy will result in better chances for her to stay focused on her impending tasks. People become Stalkers sometimes by sheer luck, but in my experience it pays to be prepared to the best of one's ability. I find it works out best if the person undergoing the training is of strong mind and master of their own will. For that reason alone, I have put a wall between myself and [S], so that she may be independent from my wants and so that any affection she might develop will not become a fatal weakness. I hope I made the right choice in doing so.\n\nIn many ways she is ready, in some, more nuanced, she is still as innocent and naive as her younger sister. Beyond that, she is truly a member of my House in every way, loyal, supportive, ready to fight to the death for each and every one of us.\n\nI have caught her bickering with her younger sister more than once... A day may soon come where I must get to the root of that resentment that seems to be piling up between them."
    new "Mi pupila, mi aprendiz y, muy posiblemente, mi sucesora, cuando sea demasiado viejo para recorrer el camino del desierto. Ha sido entrenada por mí mismo y por varios otros maestros en Zeta para convertirse en una Acechadora del Desierto por derecho propio, y el momento para que eso suceda se acerca rápidamente.\n\nSé que hay verdades y sentimientos tácitos que ambos hemos hecho a un lado para concentrarnos en sus enseñanzas. Espero que esto no se convierta en algo de lo que me arrepienta, o que pueda ponerla en peligro. Espero que sacrificar nuestra intimidad física resulte en mayores posibilidades para que ella se mantenga concentrada en sus tareas inminentes. La gente se convierte en Acechadores a veces por pura suerte, pero en mi experiencia, vale la pena estar preparado lo mejor que se pueda. Creo que funciona mejor si la persona que se somete al entrenamiento es de mente fuerte y dueña de su propia voluntad. Solo por esa razón, he puesto un muro entre [S] y yo, para que ella sea independiente de mis deseos y para que cualquier afecto que pueda desarrollar no se convierta en una debilidad fatal. Espero haber tomado la decisión correcta al hacerlo.\n\nEn muchos sentidos, ella está lista; en algunos, más sutiles, sigue siendo tan inocente e ingenua como su hermana menor. Más allá de eso, es verdaderamente un miembro de mi Casa en todos los sentidos: leal, solidaria, lista para luchar hasta la muerte por todos y cada uno de nosotros.\n\nLa he sorprendido discutiendo con su hermana menor más de una vez...\nPuede que pronto llegue el día en que deba llegar a la raíz de ese resentimiento que parece acumularse entre ellas."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:197
    old "My beloved girl... She is the youngest member of the House, having only recently come of age. Vain and a bit scatterbrained, she likes her little dresses, her jewels and to have fun. Under her childish veneer, I sense a depth that yearns to come out, and a well of insecurity about her place in the world.\n\nShe serves the House and myself well, and is completely loyal to the people she loves, her family. She is learning what it means to take responsibility for the tasks of running a household and supporting her family.\n\nAn odd mix of raw sexual energy and timid disposition, she looks up to her sister, even if she will never admit it to her. Should I be looking for a suitable partner for her, or indulge her desire to stay with us?"
    new "Mi querida niña... Es el miembro más joven de la Casa, pues acaba de cumplir la mayoría de edad. Vanidosa y un poco atolondrada, le gustan sus vestiditos, sus joyas y divertirse. Bajo su barniz infantil, percibo una profundidad que anhela salir a la luz, y un pozo de inseguridad sobre su lugar en el mundo.\n\nSirve bien a la Casa y a mí, y es completamente leal a las personas que ama, su familia. Está aprendiendo lo que significa responsabilizarse de las tareas de llevar una casa y mantener a su familia.\n\nUna extraña mezcla de energía sexual bruta y disposición tímida, admira a su hermana, aunque nunca se lo admita. ¿Debería buscarle una pareja adecuada, o consentir su deseo de quedarse con nosotros?"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:210
    old "Nadia has changed a lot since the shy girl I remember from when she used to come over to play with [A]. Seeing her all grown up reminds me a lot of her mother, back when we were younger. She has the same energy, wild streak and adventurous spirit.\n\nGrowing up in a remote village, under the roof of such a bore as Omar, she must have felt limited and stifled. I bet she's making the most of her newfound liberty here in Zeta. Omar will have a hard time trying to control her now. I guess her knowing she is not his daughter doesn't help either.\n\nI wonder if Rabiah sees herself in Nadia like I do..."
    new "Nadia ha cambiado mucho desde la niña tímida que recuerdo cuando solía venir a jugar con [A]. Verla tan crecida\nme recuerda mucho a su madre, de cuando éramos más jóvenes.\n\nAl crecer en una aldea remota, bajo el techo de un aburrido como Omar, debe haberse sentido limitada y reprimida. Apuesto a que está aprovechando al máximo su recién descubierta libertad aquí en Zeta. Omar tendrá dificultades para tratar de controlarla ahora. Supongo que el hecho de que sepa que no es su hija tampoco ayuda.\n\nMe pregunto si Rabiah se ve a sí misma en Nadia como yo lo hago..."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:222
    old "She is a slave who appears to be quite content with her status. Her heritage seems to be tied to one of the northernmost regions of Old Europe, As generations went by, she seems to retain the persistently pale skin and blonde hair of her ancestors, and even remembers some of the language they spoke. It is remarkable, what people who find themselves in slavery are able to pass on despite their hardships. Born into slavery, she has learned to be an accomplished servant and house maid; to the point that her docile nature and her skills have seen her elevated to serving at the Queen's palace. She is in fact a gift from Queen Merneith, for services rendered. I have observed her carefully, as has my wife. She gladly pledged her life and her service to my House, and by all accounts seems to be committed to proving herself. She is an adult woman, closer to my wife in age, than to my [persistent.da]s, and seems to be well versed in many ways. Her exotic looks are striking."
    new "Ella es una esclava que parece estar bastante satisfecha con su condición. Su origen parece estar relacionado con una de las regiones más al norte de la Europa Antigua. A medida que pasaron las generaciones, parece haber conservado la piel persistentemente pálida y el cabello rubio de sus antepasados, e incluso recuerda parte del idioma que hablaban. Es sorprendente lo que las personas que se encuentran en la esclavitud pueden transmitir a pesar de sus dificultades. Nacida en la esclavitud, ha aprendido a ser una sirvienta y doncella consumada; hasta el punto de que su naturaleza dócil y sus habilidades la han llevado a servir en el palacio de la Reina. De hecho, es un regalo de la Reina Merneith por los servicios prestados. La he observado con atención, al igual que mi mujer. Con gusto ofreció su vida y su servicio a mi Casa, y por lo que dicen, parece estar comprometida en demostrar su valía. Es una mujer adulta, más cercana en edad a mi mujer que a mis [persistent.da]s, y parece estar bien versada en muchos aspectos. Su aspecto exótico es impresionante."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:233
    old "I found her in chains, in the depths of the main Decayed settlement in Old Cairo. She was handed to me almost gift wrapped. A broken gift that barely spoke or seemed to understand her surroundings.\n\nI think she was abused and used for so long that a part of her took refuge in the mind of a small child-like creature, responding to basic needs by learned impulse, and running on fear rather than sustenance.\n\nAs I write this, the only thing she seems to understand is violence inflicted upon her, and she responds by trading fear with lust, clearly used to making herself available as a way to survive the day.\n\nWhat is true is that she is a remarkable beauty, with features that are uncommon and a skin that seems to bruise with exposition to the sun more than it did when she lived in the fumes of Old Cairo.\n\nHer fiery red curls are such a rarity that she would stand out even if nothing else of her was visible. Women who try to dye their hair to look like that simply never match the real deal. Time will tell what will happen to her, or whether I will grow tired of her."
    new "La encontré encadenada, en las profundidades del asentamiento principal de los Decaídos en el Viejo Cairo. Me la entregaron casi envuelta para regalo. Un regalo roto que apenas hablaba o parecía entender su entorno.\n\nCreo que fue maltratada y utilizada durante tanto tiempo que una parte de ella se refugió en la mente de un ser pequeño y de aspecto infantil, respondiendo a necesidades básicas por impulso aprendido y funcionando por miedo en lugar de subsistencia.\n\nMientras escribo esto, lo único que parece entender es la violencia infligida sobre ella, y responde intercambiando miedo por lujuria, claramente acostumbrada a ponerse a cuatro patas como una forma de sobrevivir al día.\n\nLo que es cierto es que es una belleza notable, con rasgos poco comunes y una piel que parece enrojecerse con la exposición al sol más de lo que lo hacía cuando vivía en los humos del Viejo Cairo.\n\nSus rizos pelirrojos son una rareza tal que destacaría incluso si nada más de ella fuera visible. Las mujeres que intentan teñirse el cabello para verse así simplemente nunca igualan la verdadera versión. El tiempo dirá qué le sucederá a ella o si me cansaré de ella."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:242
    old "Igor's niece, she hails from his land of origin somewhere in what used to be called Eastern Europe, which she left behind not too long ago. Igor must have told her some tall stories about me, because she seemed taken with me from the first time we met.\n\nA few occasional encounters later, I am starting to learn that the subject of pregnancy has a strong attraction for her. I have the feeling she really has an eagerness for it. Whether it's to experience the joys of motherhood or some other, more sensual expression of her desires, is maybe soon to tell.. and for some reason she seems determined to find a place in my House. My wife seems to not oppose the idea.\n\nShe has brown, shoulder-length hair and pale skin. Her smile is pretty and sweet, with eyes that seem to be always wide with excitement as she discovers new things about Zeta and its people."
    new "La sobrina de Igor, proviene de su tierra de origen en lo que solía llamarse Europa del Este, de la que se mudó no hace mucho tiempo. Igor debe de haberle contado algunas historias exageradas sobre mí, porque pareció interesada en mí desde la primera vez que nos conocimos.\n\nUnos cuantos encuentros ocasionales después, estoy empezando a descubrir que el tema del embarazo la atrae mucho. Tengo la sensación de que realmente lo ansía. Ya sea para experimentar las alegrías de la maternidad o alguna otra expresión más sensual de sus deseos, es algo que tal vez se descubra pronto... y por alguna razón parece decidida a encontrar un lugar en mi Casa. Mi esposa parece no oponerse a la idea.\n\nTiene el pelo castaño hasta los hombros y la piel pálida. Su sonrisa es bonita y dulce, con unos ojos que parecen estar siempre muy abiertos de emoción cuando descubre cosas nuevas sobre Zeta y su gente."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:250
    old "[Sh] is the Captain of Queen Merneith's personal guard and was the last Captain to serve the previous Queen in that capacity. She must be a formidable fighter, because she can't have won the position with her personality.\n\nShe seems to always be angry and confrontational, or maybe she's that way only with me. Either way, I think she doesn't like me very much and she appears to be very protective of the young Queen, more even than her position demands. Maybe she doesn't appreciate how close the Queen has let me in. I can respect that.\n\nCould it be that she's simply indoctrinated by the Temple into the cult of divinity surrounding the Queen? A true believer? I guess that would also be a factor. Anyway, I should try not to antagonize her too much, even after that little incident with my wife.\n\nShe is a tall woman with an imposing physique, lean and muscular. Just by looking at her body and the confident style of her command, it is easy to see that she has earned her position and most likely fought hard for it."
    new "[Sh] es la Capitana de la guardia personal de la Reina Merneith y fue la última Capitana en servir a la Reina anterior en ese cargo. Debe ser una luchadora formidable, porque no puede haber ganado el puesto con su personalidad.\n\nParece estar siempre cabreada y desafiante, o tal vez es así solo conmigo. De cualquier manera, creo que no le caigo muy bien y parece ser muy protectora de la joven Reina, más de lo que su posición demanda. Tal vez no aprecia cuán cerca ha dejado entrar a la Reina. Puedo respetar eso.\n\n¿Podría ser que simplemente está adoctrinada por el Templo en el culto de divinidad que rodea a la Reina? ¿Una verdadera creyente? Supongo que eso también sería un factor. De todos modos, debería tratar de no antagonizarla demasiado, incluso después de ese pequeño incidente con mi mujer.\n\nEs una mujer alta con una figura imponente, esbelta y musculosa. Solo con mirar su cuerpo y el estilo seguro de su mando, es fácil ver que ha ganado su posición y muy probablemente luchó duro por ello."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:259
    old "Ivy"
    new "Ivy"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:259
    old "She is a mysterious creature, for sure. Her pointy ears are the first thing that people mention when they refer to people like her as elves, but that is not their only distinctive trait, apparently. Ivy has learned to survive under the glare of the wasteland Sun for many years.\n\nShe is quick and extremely agile, which has obviously served her well. She keeps her hair at shoulder length, often covering part of her face as she hides in the shadows. There is just some quality to her that speak of innocence but also a potential for so much more.\n\nBy the time I am writing this, I have not yet heard Ivy speak; her eyes seem to do that for her, as they have the remarkable ability to change colour. I'm told that the colour reflects her state of mind or emotions towards individuals, but what each colour precisely means is still a mystery even for those who told me the name she seems to go by, a name they gave her.\n\nIs she loyal to the mutants who seem to rely on her abilities to find more of them? Does she have her own agenda?\n\nAll I can say is that she seems to have taken an interest in me. I will see what more I can learn about her. They tell me she does have the ability to speak, even if she does so rarely, and not with everybody."
    new "Sin duda, es una criatura misteriosa. Sus orejas puntiagudas son lo primero que menciona la gente cuando se refieren a personas como ella como elfos, pero ése no es su único rasgo distintivo, aparentemente. Ivy ha aprendido a sobrevivir bajo el resplandor del Sol de los páramos durante muchos años.\n\nEs rápida y extremadamente ágil, lo que obviamente le ha servido de mucho. Lleva el pelo a la altura de los hombros, y a menudo le cubre parte de la cara cuando se oculta en las sombras. Tiene unas cualidades que hablan de inocencia, pero también de potencial para mucho más.\n\nEn el momento en que escribo esto, aún no he oído hablar a Ivy; sus ojos parecen hacerlo por ella, ya que tienen la notable capacidad de cambiar de color. Me han dicho que el color refleja su estado de ánimo o sus emociones hacia las personas, pero lo que significa exactamente cada color sigue siendo un misterio, incluso para los que me han dicho el nombre por el que parece ir, un nombre que ellos mismos le dieron.\n\n¿Es leal a los mutantes que parecen confiar en sus habilidades para encontrar a más de ellos? ¿Tendrá sus propios planes?\n\nTodo lo que puedo decir es que parece haberse interesado por mí. Veré qué más puedo averiguar sobre ella. Me han dicho que tiene la capacidad de hablar, aunque lo hace raramente y no con todo el mundo."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:273
    old "My oldest friend and a true brother in arms. I've known his bald ass for so long now, that he feels more like a brother than a friend, and I trust him with my life and that of any of those dear to me.\n\nA generous man, a good informant, and a fairly honest merchant, wrapped in a hulking warrior's frame. I could not ask for a more loyal friend. Meeting in the middle of a bar brawl set the tone for our friendship for quite some time, but he's a more peaceful man now.\n\nWhen I first met him we were both young, and he could  barely navigate through the simplest conversations in our language, yet still he had managed to traverse the sea of sand with only a small group of travel companions. The day his passion for the desert, for seeing the world and for travel should come to an end, the city will lose a fine merchant.\n\nDecades have passed, but he still keeps that thick accent. I have to wonder if it's an affectation or if he really can't shake it. I wouldn't put it past him to have been putting it on all these years to mess with me."
    new "Mi amigo más antiguo y un verdadero hermano de armas. Conozco su cabeza calva desde hace tanto tiempo que se siente más como un hermano que como un amigo, y confío en él con mi vida y con la de cualquiera de los que me son queridos.\n\nUn hombre generoso, un buen informante y un comerciante bastante honesto, envuelto en el robusto cuerpo de un guerrero. No podría pedir un amigo más leal. Nuestro encuentro en medio de una pelea en un bar estableció el tono de nuestra amistad durante bastante tiempo, pero ahora es un hombre más pacífico.\n\nCuando lo conocí por primera vez, éramos jóvenes y apenas podía manejarse en las conversaciones más simples en nuestro idioma, y sin embargo, había logrado atravesar el mar de arena con solo un pequeño grupo de compañeros de viaje. El día en que su pasión por el desierto, por ver el mundo y por viajar llegara a su fin, la ciudad perderá a un gran comerciante.\n\nHan pasado décadas, pero aún conserva ese grueso acento. Me pregunto si es una afectación o si realmente no puede quitárselo de encima. No me extrañaría que lo haya estado fingiendo todos estos años para fastidiarme."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:284
    old "Merneith"
    new "Merneith"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:284
    old "The young Queen of Zeta. She has not been in power for long yet, a couple of years now, but, as is to be expected, her role puts her at the center of the religious beliefs of Zetans who pray to her name. She is in good standing with her subjects, who adore her as most Zetans are taught to do.\n\nI believe that she has gained their respect also, and has done so by being just and intelligent in her dealings with the city. However, she is a complex woman, with many sides to her. [S] has seen her more violent streak, her thirst for excitement.\n\nI myself have seen how she is extending her control slowly, by testing those around her and learning how to control the various people at her service. It is a good thing. A Queen should know the full extent of her powers, and the extent of the loyalty of those around her, and test those regularly.\n\nI however, have my own thoughts about whether I should or should not obey her blindly."
    new "La joven Reina de Zeta. No ha estado en el poder por mucho tiempo, un par de años hasta ahora, pero, como era de esperar, su papel la sitúa en el centro de las creencias religiosas de los zetanos que rezan a su nombre. Está en buenos términos con sus súbditos, quienes la adoran como la mayoría de los zetanos son enseñados a hacerlo.\n\nCreo que también ha ganado su respeto, y lo ha hecho siendo justa e inteligente en sus tratos con la ciudad. Sin embargo, es una mujer compleja, con muchas facetas. [S] ha visto su lado más violento, su sed de emoción.\n\nYo mismo he visto cómo está extendiendo lentamente su control, probando a quienes la rodean y aprendiendo cómo controlar a las diversas personas a su servicio. Es algo bueno. Una Reina debe conocer el alcance completo de sus poderes y la extensión de la lealtad de quienes la rodean, y probar eso regularmente.\n\nSin embargo, tengo mis propios pensamientos sobre si debo o no obedecerla ciegamente."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:299
    old "Flip Flop Ninja"
    new "El Ninja de las Sandalias"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:299
    old "Flip Flop Ninja, Guard of Zeta"
    new "El Ninja de las Sandalias, Guardia de Zeta"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:299
    old "Nobody knows his real name. All we know is that he is the stealthiest motherfucker in Zeta. He is the hero Zeta doesn't deserve, but he's all it's got."
    new "Nadie sabe su verdadero nombre. Todo lo que sabemos es que es el hijo de puta más sigiloso de Zeta. Es el héroe que Zeta no merece, pero es todo lo que tiene."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:305
    old "I am not sure why I didn't kill her when we first met. Maybe it's because she didn't seem to actually want to do me harm. Maybe she's just influenced by the wrong crowd. Her heart didn't seem to be in it.\n\nShe has a sensual voice and a body to die for, with the darkest skin contrasted by pale blue eyes clearer than my own. She is blessed with big assets in all the right places.\n\nIt's a pity she doesn't like the city, because by her looks alone, she would make a killing as a veiled lady... instead she lives off the scraps of the desert and whatever passing merchants and  Raiders share with her."
    new "No estoy seguro de por qué no la maté cuando nos conocimos por primera vez. Tal vez porque no parecía querer hacerme daño de verdad. Tal vez simplemente está influenciada por la gente equivocada. Su corazón no parecía estar en ello.\n\nTiene una voz sensual y un cuerpo para morirse, con la piel más oscura contrastada por ojos azules pálidos más claros que los míos. Está bendecida con atributos generosos en todos los lugares adecuados.\n\nEs una lástima que no le guste la ciudad, porque solo por su apariencia, podría ganar una puta fortuna como dama velada... en cambio, vive de las migajas del desierto y lo que los comerciantes y saqueadores pasajeros comparten con ella."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:314
    old "A leader of one of the gangs of Raiders, she's the younger sibling to Kyra, the top dog in her group.\n\nAs far as I know, Adira is a chaotic mess of a place, where different raider gangs control different parts of the town. The two sisters have carved their control over one of those gangs in blood. Between the two, she's the wildcat, the enforcer.\n\nProne to violence and truly embracing the raider lifestyle, she always goes all in and doesn't seem to know when to use her head.\n\nMaybe she just needs a strong hand to teach her that."
    new "Líder de una de las bandas de Asaltantes, es la hermana menor de Kyra, la jefa de su grupo.\n\nPor lo que sé, Adira es un lugar caótico, donde diferentes bandas de Asaltantes controlan distintas partes de la ciudad. Las dos hermanas se han labrado con sangre su control sobre una de esas bandas. Entre las dos, ella es la fiera, la ejecutora.\n\nPropensa a la violencia y a abrazar de verdad el estilo de vida de los asaltantes, siempre va a por todas y no parece saber cuándo usar la cabeza.\n\nQuizá sólo necesita una mano fuerte que le enseñe eso."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:324
    old "Brash, aggressive, intelligent and voracious are some of the traits this woman possesses in abundance. She's one of the leaders of the Raiders, and one of the few people of Asian descent I know.\n\nShe and her sister Asha seem to be at the head of one of the stronger Raider groups. Both have a debt towards me, and it is in my best interest to remind them of that occasionally."
    new "Descarada, agresiva, inteligente y voraz son algunos de los rasgos que esta mujer posee en abundancia. Es una de las líderes de los Asaltantes, y una de las pocas personas de ascendencia asiática que conozco.\n\nElla y su hermana Asha parecen estar a la cabeza de uno de los grupos de Asaltantes más fuertes. Ambas tienen una deuda conmigo, y me conviene recordárselo de vez en cuando."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:332
    old "I reckon that when merchants and common folk talk about the terror the Raiders represent, they must have someone like Zion in mind, a muscle-bound fury with a mean streak.\n\nShe clearly has seen some shit. Asha tells me she almost never takes off her mask and... well, she manages to keep up with the toughest of raiders despite having only one arm left to fight with.\n\nYou have to respect that, and yes, I can imagine that having her come at you screaming with a weapon must be nightmare-inducing for a weaker soul.\n\nClearly she's well respected by the other raiders, even if she seems to be amongst the most unhinged ones. I guess it's true that violence and fear are what builds a reputation in Adira. It sure explains Asha, in some ways. It's a good thing she respects Kyra enough to not fly off the handle at every turn, even if she clearly enjoys inflicting violence and torture on people.\n\nAnd what's up with that... thing she calls her boyfriend?"
    new "Creo que cuando los mercaderes y la gente común hablan del terror que representan los Asaltantes, deben tener en mente a alguien como Zion, una furia musculosa con una vena muy sádica.\n\nEstá claro que ha visto mucha mierda. Asha me dice que casi nunca se quita la máscara y... bueno, se las arregla para seguir el ritmo de los asaltantes más duros a pesar de que sólo le queda un brazo con el que luchar....\n\nTienes que respetarlo, y sí, puedo imaginar que el hecho de que se te acerque gritando con un arma debe ser una pesadilla para un alma débil.\n\nEstá claro que es muy respetada por los demás asaltantes, aunque parezca estar entre los más desquiciados. Supongo que es cierto que la violencia y el miedo son lo que forja una reputación en Adira. En cierto modo, eso explica a Asha. Menos mal que respeta a Kyra lo suficiente como para no perder los estribos a cada momento, aunque está claro que disfruta infligiendo violencia y tortura a la gente.\n\n¿Y qué pasa con esa... cosa a la que llama novio?"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:344
    old "Kitty"
    new "Kitty"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:344
    old "Now, here's something of a puzzle... I should have talked with the General for a bit, before Kyra let Zion have him. General... what a stupid name anyway. She's mute and seems to be entirely uneducated, so there's no getting anything much out of her by way of answers.\n\nShe doesn't seem frantic or anxious, or scared. She's just.. there, responsive, but passive at the same time. The pink hair is definitely a unique trait, like the blindfold.\n\nThe way I understand it, she spent most of her life as a gimmick, an object of reverence for simple-minded fools, and as a plaything to her brother who manipulated her even more than he did with those around them.\n\nShe's free from that part of her life now, but I am not sure what the future has in store for her.\n\nSat on her little blanket, she has all the energy of a sleeping puppy, and about the same degree of personality. Pretty to look at, but not very engaging at all."
    new "Ahora, aquí hay algo de rompecabezas... Debería haber hablado un poco con el General, antes de que Kyra dejara que Zion se lo quedara. General... de todas formas, qué nombre más estúpido. Es muda y parece carecer por completo de educación, así que no se le pueden sacar muchas respuestas.\n\nNo parece frenética, ni ansiosa, ni asustada. Simplemente está... ahí, receptiva, pero pasiva al mismo tiempo. El pelo rosa es definitivamente un rasgo único, como la venda en los ojos. Tal y como yo lo entiendo, pasó la mayor parte de su vida como un truco, un objeto de reverencia para tontos ingenuos, y como juguete de su hermano, que la manipulaba incluso más de lo que lo hacía con los que les rodeaban.\n\nAhora está libre de esa parte de su vida, pero no estoy seguro de lo que le depara el futuro.\n\nSentada en su mantita, tiene toda la energía de un cachorro dormido, y más o menos el mismo grado de personalidad. Bonita a la vista, pero nada atractiva."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:358
    old "Only recently have I found out that the few mutants that still live in these parts are trying to organise themselves to look out for one another. Fangs, one of their leaders, if not their main leader, is an impressive creature.\n\nTeeth as sharp as razors, which explains her name, she is a hot blooded soldier who is confrontational, physical but also strategically minded. I should try to understand her long term objectives better, and find out where she got her training from. That might give me a better insight into her personality and motives.\n\nShe does not like the Queen, for what she represents, for her role in society and the oppression of mutants that occurs in her name, but I don't think she actually thinks much about the queen herself, as a person. Under the circumstances, I can't blame her."
    new "Solo recientemente he descubierto que los pocos mutantes que aún viven en estas zonas están tratando de organizarse para velar los unos por los otros. Fangs, una de sus líderes, si no la líder principal, es una criatura impresionante.\n\nCon dientes afilados como navajas, lo que explica su nombre, es una soldado de sangre caliente, confrontativa, de acción física, pero también con mentalidad estratégica. Debería intentar comprender mejor sus objetivos a largo plazo y averiguar de dónde obtuvo su formación. Esto podría darme una mejor comprensión de su personalidad y motivos.\n\nNo le gusta la Reina, por lo que representa, por su papel en la sociedad y la opresión de los mutantes que se comete en su nombre, pero no creo que en realidad piense mucho en la reina en sí, como persona. Dadas las circunstancias, no puedo culparla."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:371
    old "I knew him, many years ago, as Zosar, my mentor, my master and the man who saw in me the potential to become a Stalker.\n\nWhen he fell ill, he took the Long Walk, and that was the last I ever thought I'd see of him. A strong fighter, a respected Elder of the city, one of the best teachers any aspiring man of arms could dream to have, he was the incarnation of all the values of Zeta.\n\nNow, I am not sure.\n\nWhat has become of him, now that he has fallen to the Decay, is something else, maybe more scary than he already was. He seems to have united under his rule many smaller groups of Decayed, which could make him into a powerful menace towards just about anyone his gaze falls upon. He has taken notice of me and my family, after all these years.\n\nI hope his ambitions are limited to the decayed and that I and the Queen shall not have to fight him, because that is a war that Zeta might not survive."
    new "Lo conocí, hace muchos años, como Zosar, mi mentor, mi maestro y el hombre que vio en mí el potencial para convertirse en un Acechador.\n\nCuando cayó enfermo, emprendió la Larga Marcha, y eso fue lo último que pensé que vería de él. Un fuerte luchador, un respetado Anciano de la ciudad, uno de los mejores maestros que cualquier aspirante a hombre de armas podría soñar tener, era la encarnación de todos los valores de Zeta.\n\nAhora, no estoy seguro.\n\nLo que ha sido de él, ahora que ha caído en la Decadencia, es otra cosa, quizá más temible de lo que ya era. Parece haber reunido bajo su dominio a muchos grupos menores de Decaídos, lo que podría convertirle en una poderosa amenaza para cualquiera sobre el que caiga su mirada. Se ha fijado en mí y en mi familia, después de todos estos años.\n\nEspero que sus ambiciones se limiten a los Decaídos y que yo y la Reina no tengamos que luchar contra él, porque ésa es una guerra a la que Zeta podría no sobrevivir."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:386
    old "Zetans"
    new "Los Zetanos"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:386
    old "Zetan society is both complex and simple. Ruled by principles of strength, respect of traditions and a delicate balancing act of knowing your place and how far you can extend your free will, it's a city were everybody has a function and a place, an opportunity and an obligation.\n\nThe Queen is the ultimate ruler of the city, its religious authority and the head of the Palace. The Temple, the army, the bureaucrats and the Elders all respond to her, at least nominally. All of Zeta is, or must show to be, loyal to the Queen, who administers justice according to the few laws and traditions we hold sacred. How much of that absolute power actually has an effect beyond the confines of the palace, and how much of her decisions are filtered, interpreted or guided by her inner Council, the Elders, remains in question. It's one of the many secrets of the Palace.\n\nThe common folk of Zeta are concerned more with day to day things such as finding a way to thrive and survive. Some choose to serve the Sacred City, in a variety of functions, for example by joining the army, or the Temple. Some are merchants, traders, or craftsmen and women who produce all manners of goods. Zeta is fortunate compared to the smaller places that surround it. The city is older than most other settlements, and has had a head start when it comes to irrigating fields, cultivating crops, mining for resources or establishing relations with other countries or cities far from Egypt. With wealth comes population, and the ability to invest resources in developing better living conditions.\n\nOf course it helps that slavery is a thing. War prisoners, debtors, people born into slavery, criminals who must serve a sentence, people who trade the security of three meals a day for their freedom, in order to escape abject poverty... even abduction from other areas; there are many ways in which one becomes a slave in Zeta, and it's undeniable that the cheap labour has helped bolstering the city's fortunes.\n\nIn a world where lives are ruled by scarcity, violence and sometimes desperation, Zeta, flawed as it may be, is a better place than most, provided you can stand up for yourself, make your mark and defend what's yours. Might makes right here, sometimes more so than in other places; but contrary to most other places, in Zeta, might is not always expressed by the strength of one's blade. It IS possible to make a decent and honest living and be shielded from violence, letting the guards and the soldiers protect you, and if that's not a display of might that the common folk have, what is?\n\nIn the end, some sense of civilisation has been conquered here, over the last centuries, and Zetans have a right to be proud people.\n\nThat said, I don't know if I feel at home in Zeta, or that I have a real place in it. I have spent most of my life with a blade in hand and I am used to being master of myself and my House, so bending the knee to the authority of the Queen does not come easy. On the other hand, it is undeniable that the mere existence of Zeta represents a safety net for me and my people, should things turn for the worse. And it is still a resource for protection, opportunity and alliances."
    new "Nuestra sociedad Zetana es a la vez compleja y simple. Está gobernada por principios de fuerza, respeto a las tradiciones y un delicado equilibrio entre conocer tu lugar y hasta dónde puedes ejercer tu libre albedrío. Es una ciudad donde todos tienen una función y un lugar, una oportunidad y una obligación.\n\nLa Reina es la gobernante suprema de la ciudad, su autoridad religiosa y la cabeza del Palacio. El Templo, el ejército, los burócratas y los Ancianos todos responden a ella, al menos nominalmente. Todo Zeta es, o debe mostrar ser, leal a la Reina, quien administra la justicia de acuerdo con las pocas leyes y tradiciones que consideramos sagradas. Cuánto de ese poder absoluto tiene un efecto más allá de los confines del palacio, y cuántas de sus decisiones son filtradas, interpretadas o guiadas por su Consejo interno, los Ancianos, sigue siendo una incógnita. Es uno de los muchos secretos del Palacio.\n\nLa gente común de Zeta se preocupa más por las cosas cotidianas, como encontrar una forma de prosperar y sobrevivir. Algunos eligen servir a la Ciudad Sagrada en diversas funciones, como unirse al ejército o al Templo. Algunos son mercaderes, comerciantes o artesanos y artesanas que producen todo tipo de bienes. Zeta es afortunada en comparación con los lugares más pequeños que la rodean. La ciudad es más antigua que la mayoría de los demás asentamientos y ha tenido una ventaja en cuanto a la irrigación de campos, el cultivo de cosechas, la extracción de recursos o el establecimiento de relaciones con otros países o ciudades lejanas de Egipto. Con la riqueza viene la población y la capacidad de invertir recursos en el desarrollo de mejores condiciones de vida.\n\nPor supuesto, la esclavitud es una realidad. Prisioneros de guerra, deudores, personas nacidas en la esclavitud, criminales que deben cumplir una condena, personas que comercian la seguridad de tres comidas al día por su libertad, con el fin de escapar de la pobreza extrema... incluso el secuestro en otras áreas; hay muchas formas en las que uno se convierte en esclavo en Zeta, y es innegable que el trabajo barato ha ayudado a fortalecer la fortuna de la ciudad.\n\nEn un mundo donde la vida está regida por la escasez, la violencia y a veces la desesperación, Zeta, con todos sus defectos, es un lugar mejor que la mayoría, siempre y cuando puedas defenderte, dejar tu huella y proteger lo que es tuyo. Aquí el poder es la ley, a veces más que en otros lugares; pero a diferencia de la mayoría de los demás lugares, en Zeta, la fuerza no siempre se expresa por la fuerza de su espada. Es posible ganarse la vida decentemente y honestamente y estar protegido de la violencia, dejando que los guardias y los soldados te protejan, y si eso no es una demostración de fuerza que la gente común tiene, ¿qué es?\n\nAl final, algo de civilización se ha conquistado aquí en los últimos siglos, y los zetanos tienen derecho a ser un pueblo orgulloso.\n\nDicho esto, no estoy seguro de sentirme en casa en Zeta, o de tener un lugar real en él. He pasado la mayor parte de mi vida con una espada en la mano y estoy acostumbrado a ser el dueño de mí mismo y de mi Casa, así que doblar la rodilla ante la autoridad de la Reina no es fácil. Por otro lado, es innegable que la mera existencia de Zeta representa una red de seguridad para mí y mi gente, en caso de que las cosas se pongan peor. Y sigue siendo un recurso para la protección, las oportunidades y las alianzas."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:418
    old "Raiders"
    new "Asaltantes"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:418
    old "They are the outlaws, the bandits and the ravagers of our society. It's an odd way to look at it, because there are so few real laws that regulate the lives of the people of Zeta. Just like Zetans, Raiders respect power above all, and that should bring us close, but they do bring an element of chaos to everything they touch.\n\nThey care little for farming, animal rearing, learning crafts or building something for tomorrow. Their children are tossed together in a heap, and must learn to fend for themselves, half feral.\n\nViolence, to them, is more than a way to regulate the balance of power as it is to Zeta, it's a way of life, sometimes the only thing they pursue and understand. Raiding parties are how they find the means to their survival, hitting smaller settlements, sometimes even the Decayed.\n\nThey have all concentrated in a shanty town they have called Adira. It's build on the bed of what once was the Sacred Nile, and made in large part of old containers and empty hulls of ships.\n\nThey seem to be divided in a handful of factions that control different parts of the town.. I think many of them are either rejects from Zeta or the descendants of such rejects."
    new "Son los forajidos, los bandidos y los asaltantes de nuestra sociedad. Es una forma extraña de verlo, porque hay muy pocas leyes reales que regulen la vida de los habitantes de Zeta. Al igual que los zetanos, los Asaltantes respetan el poder por encima de todo, y eso debería acercarnos, pero aportan un elemento de caos a todo lo que tocan.\n\nSe preocupan poco por la agricultura, la cría de animales, el aprendizaje de oficios o la construcción de algo para el mañana. Sus hijos están amontonados y deben aprender a valerse por sí mismos, medio asilvestrados.\n\nLa violencia, para ellos, es más que una forma de regular el equilibrio de poder como lo es para los zetanos, es una forma de vida, a veces lo único que persiguen y entienden. Las partidas de asalto son la forma en que encuentran los medios para su supervivencia, golpeando asentamientos más pequeños, a veces incluso a los Decaídos.\n\nSe han concentrado todos en un poblado de chabolas al que han llamado Adira. Está construida sobre el lecho de lo que una vez fue el Nilo Sagrado, y hecha en gran parte de viejos contenedores y cascos vacíos de barcos.\n\nParecen estar divididos en un puñado de facciones que controlan diferentes partes de la ciudad. Creo que muchos de ellos son rechazados de Zeta o descendientes de dichos rechazados."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:435
    old "Mutants"
    new "Mutantes"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:435
    old "Nobody truly knows how mutants come to be, but it is said that no family is safe from the risk of potentially giving birth to a mutant. To be fair however, in my living memory, I do not recall hearing of a mutant that was not born to a slave. I guess their bloodline must have been bred out of the Citizens.\n\nAlmost all of the mutants alive in the city are women. That's primarily because male mutants rarely survive childhood. Almost always born into slavery, a male mutant is seen as a waste of resources and a potential menace, So they are either killed outright or put to die in the Arena.\n\nI have yet to see a mutant gain status of citizen, but maybe, now that they have found some resources that seem to be beyond anything that Zeta can put on the battlefield, they can leverage those resources to find a place to themselves, and a seat at the table, should they want it. For now however, it seems they are in disarray and still a long way away from being organised to the point of becoming a menace.\n\nThey have approached me, but I wonder what their plans are, both for me and for their fight for recognition. Caution is the word of the day."
    new "Nadie sabe realmente cómo surgen los mutantes, pero se dice que ninguna familia está a salvo del riesgo de dar a luz a un mutante. Sin embargo, para ser justos, en mi memoria viva, no recuerdo haber oído hablar de un mutante que no haya nacido de un esclavo. Supongo que su línea de sangre debe haber sido criada fuera de los Ciudadanos.\n\nLa mayoría de los mutantes vivos en la ciudad son mujeres. Eso se debe principalmente a que los mutantes masculinos rara vez sobreviven a la infancia. Casi siempre nacen en la esclavitud, un mutante masculino es visto como un desperdicio de recursos y una amenaza potencial, así que se les mata directamente o se les pone a morir en la Arena.\n\nTodavía no he visto que un mutante obtenga el estatus de ciudadano, pero tal vez, ahora que han encontrado algunos recursos que parecen estar por encima de cualquier cosa que Zeta pueda poner en el campo de batalla, puedan aprovechar esos recursos para encontrar un lugar para sí mismos, y un asiento en la mesa, si lo quieren. Sin embargo, por ahora parece que están desorganizados y aún están muy lejos de estar organizados hasta el punto de convertirse en una amenaza.\n\nSe han acercado a mí, pero me pregunto cuáles son sus planes, tanto para mí como para su lucha por el reconocimiento. Precaución es la palabra del día."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:452
    old "The Decayed"
    new "Los Decaídos"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:452
    old "Under the name Decayed, or Damned, we count those who have somehow adapted to the corrupting illness that kills so many of us. They are often disfigured, hairless and gaunt, their lifespans, if you can call it such, extended by several decades.\n\nIt is said they are monsters who feast on human flesh, and I have had the opportunity to verify this, it is true. However, it seems to me they would be perfectly happy to eat something else, if there were enough resources for everybody. This not being the case, they seem to have adapted fairly well and learned not to let such gruesome circumstances bother them.\n\nThey live and thrive without issue in the most polluted and corrupted environments, which is why their main strongholds are to be found in places such as Old Cairo, where no other living creature could survive. They have been around for decades, centuries even, some say they go back to the End of Days, but nobody knows for certain.\n\nWhat is known about them is that they don't reproduce sexually, which begs the question how their numbers keep growing lately. My best guess is that they recruit those unfortunate enough to fall prey to the toxic wastes and the cursed corrupting winds.\n\nUntil a few decades ago they were mostly divided in small groups that would live on the margins of civilisation, but they seem to have found a common ground lately, and to have found ways to organise themselves in larger factions and groups.\n\nThey look down upon the mindless mummies that infest many ancient places, yet they are in some ways, kin."
    new "Bajo el nombre de Decaídos, o Condenados, se cuentan los que se han adaptado de alguna manera a la enfermedad corruptora que mata a tantos de nosotros. Suelen estar desfigurados, sin pelo y demacrados, y su esperanza de vida, si puede llamarse así, se prolonga varias décadas.\n\nSe dice que son monstruos que se dan un festín de carne humana, y he tenido ocasión de comprobarlo, es cierto. Sin embargo, me parece que estarían perfectamente contentos de comer otra cosa, si hubiera recursos suficientes para todos. Al no ser así, parece que se han adaptado bastante bien y han aprendido a no dejar que esas horribles circunstancias les molesten.\n\nViven y prosperan sin problemas en los entornos más contaminados y corruptos, por lo que sus principales bastiones se encuentran en lugares como el Viejo Cairo, donde ningún otro ser vivo podría sobrevivir. Llevan décadas, incluso siglos, algunos dicen que se remontan al Fin de los Días, pero nadie lo sabe con certeza.\n\nLo que se sabe de ellos es que no se reproducen sexualmente, lo que lleva a preguntarse cómo sigue creciendo su número últimamente. Mi mejor conjetura es que reclutan a aquellos lo suficientemente desafortunados como para ser presa de los desechos tóxicos y de los malditos vientos corruptores.\n\nHasta hace unas décadas estaban divididos en su mayoría en pequeños grupos que vivían al margen de la civilización, pero parece que últimamente han encontrado un terreno común, y han hallado la forma de organizarse en facciones y grupos más grandes.\n\nMiran con desprecio a las momias descerebradas que infestan muchos lugares antiguos, pero en cierto modo son parientes."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:472
    old "Reflections on Zeta"
    new "Reflexiones sobre Zeta"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:472
    old "Reflections on Zeta, the city of Queens."
    new "Reflexiones sobre Zeta, la ciudad de las Reinas."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:472
    old "Under the shadows of the Palace and the Temple, I was born into this bastion of civilisation in a dry land scoured by raiders, mummies, decayed, and ravaged by storms of all manners.\n\nThe city was founded, legends say, by the first Queen Merneith. We are taught that she is the conduit between the Gods and the people.\n\n- Personal records, D 4, Y 425 since the Founding of Zeta"
    new "Bajo las sombras del Palacio y el Templo, nací en este bastión de la civilización en una tierra árida, surcada por asaltantes, momias, decaídos y asolada por tormentas de todo tipo.\n\nLa ciudad fue fundada, según las leyendas, por la primera reina Merneith. Nos enseñan que ella es el conducto entre los dioses y el pueblo.\n\n- Registros personales, D 4, Y 425 desde la fundación de Zeta"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:481
    old "Old Cairo"
    new "El Viejo Cairo"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:481
    old "Thousands of years ago, the city of Cairo represented one of the wonders of the world. Ancient Pharaos ruled the Nile from their palaces of stone and erected monuments that would stand the test of time.\n\nThose monuments are still there, and stand alone, pock marking the land of Egypt as stark reminders of not one but two bygone civilisations. The Nile has either evaporated or sunken into the ground when the End of Days came and cracked open the heaven and the earth.\n\nThe riverbed is now a wasteland, where nothing grows and the sea itself, for ages a toxic bubbling mass, has retreated from the city.\n\nAll that remains in the city is a slew of decaying buildings, toppled and leaning on one another, as bits and pieces fall from them over the years, leaving often nought but a frame of what was once a tall high-rise, a bustling market, a tall office center.\n\nWe know these things because people like me, occasionally, explore those places looking for interesting artifacts; never staying long enough to let radiation, decay or illness catch us.\n\nOnly the Decayed have made their nest there and are slowly rebuilding parts of the city to suit their monstrous needs. Mummies roam some of the buildings, but they hardly constitute a problem, except when they concentrate in too large numbers to confront.\n\nOccasionally, even a few mutant creatures have been spotted searching through the rubble for something to eat. Their nature defends them from the worst effects of the place, or maybe the effects are what has turned them in such abominations.\n\nWhat turned a once bustling city into ground zero for the worst storms that ravage our lands, is unknown."
    new "Hace miles de años, la ciudad del Cairo representaba una de las maravillas del mundo. Los antiguos faraones gobernaban el Nilo desde sus palacios de piedra y erigían monumentos que resistirían la prueba del tiempo.\n\nEsos monumentos siguen ahí, y se mantienen solos, marcando la tierra de Egipto como duros recordatorios no de una sino de dos civilizaciones pasadas. El Nilo se ha evaporado o se ha hundido en el suelo cuando llegó el Fin de los Días y abrió el cielo y la tierra.\n\nEl lecho del río es ahora un páramo, donde no crece nada y el propio mar, durante mucho tiempo una masa tóxica burbujeante, se ha retirado de la ciudad. \n\nTodo lo que queda en la ciudad es un montón de edificios en decadencia, derrumbados y apoyados unos sobre otros, ya que los trozos se desprenden de ellos a lo largo de los años, dejando a menudo nada más que un marco de lo que una vez fue un alto rascacielos, un bullicioso mercado, un alto centro de oficinas. \n\nSabemos estas cosas porque la gente como yo, de vez en cuando, explora esos lugares en busca de artefactos interesantes; nunca nos quedamos lo suficiente como para dejar que la radiación, la decadencia o la enfermedad nos atrapen.\n\nSólo los Decaídos han hecho su nido allí y están reconstruyendo lentamente partes de la ciudad para adaptarlas a sus monstruosas necesidades. Las momias deambulan por algunos edificios, pero apenas constituyen un problema, excepto cuando se concentran en un número demasiado grande como para enfrentarse a ellas.\n\nDe vez en cuando, incluso se han visto algunas criaturas mutantes buscando entre los escombros algo que comer. Su naturaleza les defiende de los peores efectos del lugar, o tal vez sean los efectos los que les han convertido en tales abominaciones.\n\nSe desconoce qué ha convertido una ciudad antaño bulliciosa en la zona cero de las peores tormentas que asolan nuestras tierras."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:503
    old "Adira"
    new "Adira"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:503
    old "Calling it a city is a compliment. This is not Zeta. It's a ragtag bunch of buildings, put together using old containers, discarded or looted panels and all manner of waste materials.\n\nThere doesn't seem to be a center or a common area, despite a couple of stranded container ships from before the End of Days being used as a base by some of the gangs that rule the city.\n\nIt's divided in an ever shifting number of mid to large gangs that take hold of a portion of the city until someone else stronger rises and challenges their control.\n\nBloody, savage and unrepentantly vicious, its inhabitants live off the proceeds of their raids, mostly, which does make them outcasts of more civilised places such as Zeta or the smaller villages in the surroundings.\n\nI've been there a couple of times in the past, but haven't had cause to return, until very recently."
    new "Llamarla ciudad es un cumplido. Esto no es Zeta. Es un montón de edificios desordenados, construidos con viejos contenedores, paneles desechados o saqueados y todo tipo de materiales de desecho.\n\nNo parece haber un centro o una zona común, a pesar de que un par de barcos contenedores varados de antes del Fin de los Días son utilizados como base por algunas de las bandas que gobiernan la ciudad.\n\nEstá dividida en un número siempre cambiante de bandas medianas y grandes que se apoderan de una parte de la ciudad hasta que alguien más fuerte se levanta y desafía su control.\n\nSangrientos, salvajes e impenitentemente despiadados, sus habitantes viven principalmente de las ganancias de sus incursiones, lo que los convierte en parias de lugares más civilizados como Zeta o los pueblos más pequeños de los alrededores.\n\nHe estado allí un par de veces en el pasado, pero no he tenido motivos para volver, hasta hace muy poco."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:516
    old "The Sapa"
    new "The Sapa"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:516
    old "This is the family of Pepper and Chili. They're a semi-nomadic tribe who have managed to preserve a lot of knowledge of things from the past, especially science related things, which I guess goes a long way to explain how Pepper was able to make use of so many parts of the bunker that I could only stare at in confusion.\n\nI don't have the knowledge of whether their condition is a mutation or a curse, or some other form of anomaly. I don't even know if it can be called a condition. They tell me that from a very young age, they are able to determine at what age they will pass away, provided this is left to natural causes. I can't tell if that's a terrible thing to know, or a blessing. What would I do if I was in the same situation as, say, Chili?\n\nTheir connection with the mutants in the bunker is going to shape their destiny, one way or another."
    new "This is the family of Pepper and Chili. They're a semi-nomadic tribe who have managed to preserve a lot of knowledge of things from the past, especially science related things, which I guess goes a long way to explain how Pepper was able to make use of so many parts of the bunker that I could only stare at in confusion.\n\nI don't have the knowledge of whether their condition is a mutation or a curse, or some other form of anomaly. I don't even know if it can be called a condition. They tell me that from a very young age, they are able to determine at what age they will pass away, provided this is left to natural causes. I can't tell if that's a terrible thing to know, or a blessing. What would I do if I was in the same situation as, say, Chili?\n\nTheir connection with the mutants in the bunker is going to shape their destiny, one way or another."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:527
    old "The Hive"
    new "The Hive"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:527
    old "These creatures are an aberration. They are human in appearance but by all other metric they behave like an ant colony. T hey're neither fully human nor decayed, but if ever a mutation found itself halfway between those two, this would be it, I guess.\n\nThe mother exerts absolute control over the men in the hive, I think through the use of her voice, to which they seem extremely sensitive. Her daughter seems to carry the same powers and be somehow aware of the mother's state of mind and wellbeing even when she's a considerable distance away... or maybe that's just how she expresses herself when she's worried about her. It is hard to say."
    new "These creatures are an aberration. They are human in appearance but by all other metric they behave like an ant colony. T hey're neither fully human nor decayed, but if ever a mutation found itself halfway between those two, this would be it, I guess.\n\nThe mother exerts absolute control over the men in the hive, I think through the use of her voice, to which they seem extremely sensitive. Her daughter seems to carry the same powers and be somehow aware of the mother's state of mind and wellbeing even when she's a considerable distance away... or maybe that's just how she expresses herself when she's worried about her. It is hard to say."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:536
    old "There is something unsettling about this woman. I am blessed for being surrounded and affording the company of many of the most beautiful women of the realm and beyond. I've bedded and enjoyed their favours.\n\nThis one is different. She is not more pretty than the Queen, nor as enticing and sensual as my wife. Her eyes aren't like those of Shani or Ivy; she is not as open and brazen as Ain, yet somehow seems to contain the sum of those parts and be both more and less at the same time.\n\nThere's some force that seems to attract all attention towards her whenever she's in the room, a force she seems able to manipulate and turn on when she needs it.\n\nThe truth is that people wouldn't notice at first sight, as her mutation, that long tongue of hers, is what would catch one's attention first... but once one pays attention to it, it's unmissable.\n\nIf that is the core of her mutant nature, she can certainly be a serious danger to any red-blooded person who might fall under her spell."
    new "There is something unsettling about this woman. I am blessed for being surrounded and affording the company of many of the most beautiful women of the realm and beyond. I've bedded and enjoyed their favours.\n\nThis one is different. She is not more pretty than the Queen, nor as enticing and sensual as my wife. Her eyes aren't like those of Shani or Ivy; she is not as open and brazen as Ain, yet somehow seems to contain the sum of those parts and be both more and less at the same time.\n\nThere's some force that seems to attract all attention towards her whenever she's in the room, a force she seems able to manipulate and turn on when she needs it.\n\nThe truth is that people wouldn't notice at first sight, as her mutation, that long tongue of hers, is what would catch one's attention first... but once one pays attention to it, it's unmissable.\n\nIf that is the core of her mutant nature, she can certainly be a serious danger to any red-blooded person who might fall under her spell."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:548
    old "Elvira, the woman I know as Pepper is a brilliant mind wrapped in a stunning body. Her intelligence and scientific approach almost make her a relic from a more knowledgeable past.\n\nShe might let me get away with my little games, but I have no doubt that she is focused on her research and on reviving knowledge once available to everybody. In the eyes of Zetan traditionalist, she should probably be put to death.\n\nI guess that, and access to the resources of the bunker, the lab in particular, explains why she would leave her people, especially to help her little sister. She too shares that same mutation, after all, and is perfectly suited to find a way to counter it, if there is any to be found. I wonder why Fangs gave her that name, when she mostly acts like a cold fish towards everybody."
    new "Elvira, the woman I know as Pepper is a brilliant mind wrapped in a stunning body. Her intelligence and scientific approach almost make her a relic from a more knowledgeable past.\n\nShe might let me get away with my little games, but I have no doubt that she is focused on her research and on reviving knowledge once available to everybody. In the eyes of Zetan traditionalist, she should probably be put to death.\n\nI guess that, and access to the resources of the bunker, the lab in particular, explains why she would leave her people, especially to help her little sister. She too shares that same mutation, after all, and is perfectly suited to find a way to counter it, if there is any to be found. I wonder why Fangs gave her that name, when she mostly acts like a cold fish towards everybody."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:559
    old "I have to think that Fangs has a sense of humour after all, given how she chooses the nicknames of the people who she gives shelter to in the bunker. Her actual name is Mina, but Chili does fit her. Pepper's sister is something of a puzzle.\n\nShe's young and full of energy, yet the foreknowledge of her fate seems to bring her a sense of stability and wisdom beyond her young age.\n\nEven so, youthful exuberance and the same inquisitive mind as her sister give her an unique temperament. If only her taste in music wasn't so... loud."
    new "I have to think that Fangs has a sense of humour after all, given how she chooses the nicknames of the people who she gives shelter to in the bunker. Her actual name is Mina, but Chili does fit her. Pepper's sister is something of a puzzle.\n\nShe's young and full of energy, yet the foreknowledge of her fate seems to bring her a sense of stability and wisdom beyond her young age.\n\nEven so, youthful exuberance and the same inquisitive mind as her sister give her an unique temperament. If only her taste in music wasn't so... loud."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:569
    old "The Stalkers"
    new "The Stalkers"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:569
    old "According to my old master, Zosar, the story of the Stalkers is about as old as the City itself. When the first Zones appeared, shortly after the End of Days, the early settlers of Zeta were caught by surprise.\n\nThe story goes that a small pocket of what seemed to be another world appeared to replace a stretch of land very close to the settlements. It only stayed in existence for maybe a week, but people who ventured into it or who were there when it first appeared seemed to disappear into thin air. Only a few individuals managed to escape the affected area and were rendered insane by the experience. When next it happened, a few of the more worldly and experienced settlers grouped together and entered this new Zone. Here they found themselves in a hilly region, lush with abundant grass and water. They explored for a while, getting lost in the process, turned about by twists and bends in the landscape. Finally they were attacked by what they described as monstruous mutations of humanlike creatures and had to fight for their lives. Only two people survived.\n\nThey later became the first ones to repeatedly explore Zones as they appeared. After a falling out, one of them started training a new generation of explorers, focusing on learning to move with stealth and circumspection, which led to them being called Stalkers, whereas the other chose to abandon the City.\n\nThe latter was seen, over the years, as he explored new Zones, either by himself or with a group of recruits. Over time, the Stalkers of Zeta developed a tight bond with the City leadership, receiving benefits, lodging, resources, in exchange for sharing what they discovered, whereas other people, whether tied to the renegade Stalker or independently, approached the Zones primarily to loot anything they could, scavenge any resource they found, without really caring for the preservation of knowledge they could acquire during those explorations.\n\nI myself have been guilty of the occasional looting, it is, after all, how I make a living, but I do pride myself on trying to accumulate and preserve whatever knowledge of our past I can find."
