    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:588
    old "The Overpass"
    new "The Overpass"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:588
    old "The origin of the name is clear, since it's build on and under what remains of a bridge, or an overpass, part of a stretch of a road dating back from before our time.\n\nDespite mostly lacking in a natural source of water, the settlement is located there because it sits right next to a mine, a large crater where people slave every day to retrieve a few pounds of ore to sell. It's hard work and the settlement is something of a refuge for loners and desperate people who don't fit in in most other places.\n\nIt was controlled and exploited by a man who called himself the General, who has since been deposed and, let's say, terminated, by Kyra's merry gang of Raiders, who I have managed to convince to take over the settlement rather than raiding it into the ground.\n\nSince it's along one of the trading routes, the Queen has taken an interest also, which is why she instructed me to inspect that place in the first place."
    new "The origin of the name is clear, since it's build on and under what remains of a bridge, or an overpass, part of a stretch of a road dating back from before our time.\n\nDespite mostly lacking in a natural source of water, the settlement is located there because it sits right next to a mine, a large crater where people slave every day to retrieve a few pounds of ore to sell. It's hard work and the settlement is something of a refuge for loners and desperate people who don't fit in in most other places.\n\nIt was controlled and exploited by a man who called himself the General, who has since been deposed and, let's say, terminated, by Kyra's merry gang of Raiders, who I have managed to convince to take over the settlement rather than raiding it into the ground.\n\nSince it's along one of the trading routes, the Queen has taken an interest also, which is why she instructed me to inspect that place in the first place."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:598
    old "The caves of Zeta"
    new "The caves of Zeta"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:598
    old "I am Mahmoud, Master of the Caves, servant of our Queen and of the glory of Zeta. Hear my final wisdom, my son. The title I bear is older than memory. Our forefather helped raise the first walls of the City and became the first Master of the Caves when the hidden waters beneath Zeta were discovered after the End of Days. The duty entrusted to him was a challenging one: to create a filtration system that would divert some of the flowing water into smaller basins and purify it there. Mapping out the new, sprawling underground flow of the sacred Nile was his first great accomplishment. Then he put together a chain of machines that would modify the composition of rocks lining the caves, so that they would cleanse the water collected in these pools. He taught his son how to care for the machines that did the work, and he did the same, in time, with his firstborn. The knowledge passed from father to son until it came to me. You have often wondered why I never taught you the secrets to these machines. Now I may tell you. There are no secrets left.\n\nThe engines are winding down, because they have accomplished their purpose. In all the Chambers of Growing, a composition of minerals is perforated and sculpted in just such a way as to create a permeable barrier that will only allow water to pass that has been filtered through it to an acceptable level of purity, before it reaches the irrigation ditches. Left without a purpose, their service comes to an end, and so does mine. The waters beneath the City are clean. Others can tend them now. The Houses of Healing will safeguard the reservoirs, the wells, the public's rationed access to water, and the Chambers of Growing will continue to be irrigated as they have so far. Only one thing will be lost. When the last engine stops, the hum that has echoed beneath Zeta for centuries will vanish. What has come to be known as the Song of the City will fall silent. I have lived my life in service to that Song. When it ends, I shall relinquish my office and, as commanded by the Queen, my life. It is time to put the final incongruence to rest, and to step into the world as it is intended, finally shunning the last remnant of the technologies that have caused the End of Days. To complete the final steps, I have destroyed the manuals and records of our line, as there is no purpose left to them. Since the death of the Song will be by necessity an event that will affect people profoundly, it must not happen in a void. A narrative must exist whereby the divine song's disappearance is explained. For this, a villain must be found. I shall be that villain and shall bear the mark of shame. I shall be publicly accused and found guilty of destroying the Song, and my death shall serve as a satisfying morale, so that nobody might question events, or seek for other explanations as to the end of the Song.\n\nFor this, I raised you to be a merchant, not a cleric or indeed my successor. Use the connections you have made through my office and, when they come to destroy my name, detach yourself from my legacy and secure the future of our House. A list of names accompanies this letter. Forgive this old man the distance he placed between us. It was meant to shield you from what is to come. When you have read these words, destroy them. Let the past rest. I am Mahmoud, son of Mahmoud, last Master of the Caves. This is my wisdom."
