    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:630
    old "Death of the Song"
    new "Death of the Song"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:630
    old "The story is told that the Gods shaped the people and the sacred City of Zeta in Song. In those first ages, the City lived beneath its melody. Children were born to it, and men and women took comfort in its eternal hum. Then came the traitor, whose name has been stricken from all records. His name is not spoken, nor shall it be written. He performed a forbidden rite and severed the Song from us. The Queen had him seized and cast into the newly raised Arena, where justice was made final. Some say this marked the coming of age of the sacred City, the end of innocence and the beginning of wisdom. But among the faithful it is spoken otherwise. For the Song was not mere comfort, but proof of the gods' presence among us. Its silence has not weakened belief, yet it has deepened uncertainty. If one man could silence the voice of the divine, what assurance remains that our prayers are heard? That our devotion is received? That the soul is held beyond death? We sing still, though the Song does not answer. And in the silence that follows, the heart grows heavy. Cursed be the hand that severed us from the gods' voice."
    new "The story is told that the Gods shaped the people and the sacred City of Zeta in Song. In those first ages, the City lived beneath its melody. Children were born to it, and men and women took comfort in its eternal hum. Then came the traitor, whose name has been stricken from all records. His name is not spoken, nor shall it be written. He performed a forbidden rite and severed the Song from us. The Queen had him seized and cast into the newly raised Arena, where justice was made final. Some say this marked the coming of age of the sacred City, the end of innocence and the beginning of wisdom. But among the faithful it is spoken otherwise. For the Song was not mere comfort, but proof of the gods' presence among us. Its silence has not weakened belief, yet it has deepened uncertainty. If one man could silence the voice of the divine, what assurance remains that our prayers are heard? That our devotion is received? That the soul is held beyond death? We sing still, though the Song does not answer. And in the silence that follows, the heart grows heavy. Cursed be the hand that severed us from the gods' voice."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:645
    old "Desert Storms"
    new "Tormentas del Desierto"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:645
    old "{i}From conversations with a tribesman{/i}\n\nWe are the people of the desert, the bedouin. We know about storms. Our clothes, our tents, our every possession, even our animals; we know about storms. Sand storms, as big as the mind can fathom, clouding the horizon with dust and wind and terror; we have this in our blood. We do not fear the storm and I know you don't either.\n\nEven so, most of us have left for the southern regions and few of us still travel these lands. Even the depths of the Sahara see the occasional flash rain flood. This thing you have here, with the red corrupting mist and the poisoning of the lungs... I do not know how you cling to life, how you endure. This is different from what I know. The green dry clouds, the waterless rain, the death of the sacred Nile, whose bed lies as barren as a dead tree... You must have offended the djinns.\n\nDeath has gripped these lands, and will not let it go, but maybe there is some hope to be found. I have learned that many of you fear the green storm and call it cursed. I have learned that when the green storm strikes, you cover your heads, close your doors, shutter your windows, and pray to the gods of your fathers, for deliverance. I do not know that this is right.\n\nI have seen the land. I have spoken to it. I have spoken to those that live off the land and try to farm it or know of such things. They tell me that there is life in the land, when the storm has passed; life that was scarcely there before the storm. Our elders speak of days in which the sky was clear, and blue like the garments of our women, and the Sun shone bright over our heads.\n\nI pray that I may see the blue sky above the big cities before my passing. I pray for you, Stalker of these lands, that you may see it as well. Be at peace."
    new "{i}De las conversaciones con un miembro de la tribu{/i}\n\nNosotros somos la gente del desierto, los beduinos. Conocemos las tormentas. Nuestras ropas, nuestras tiendas, todas nuestras posesiones, incluso nuestros animales; conocemos las tormentas. Las tormentas de arena, tan grandes como la mente puede comprender, nublando el horizonte con polvo y viento y terror; lo llevamos en la sangre. No tememos a la tormenta y sé que tú tampoco.\n\nAún así, la mayoría de nosotros se ha marchado a las regiones del sur y son pocos los que siguen recorriendo estas tierras. Incluso en las profundidades del Sahara se producen ocasionalmente inundaciones por lluvias torrenciales. Esto que tenéis aquí, con la niebla roja corruptora y el envenenamiento de los pulmones... No sé cómo os aferráis a la vida, cómo aguantáis. Esto es diferente de lo que yo conozco. Las nubes verdes y secas, la lluvia sin agua, la muerte del sagrado Nilo, cuyo lecho yace tan estéril como un árbol muerto... Debes haber ofendido a los djinns.\n\nLa muerte se ha apoderado de estas tierras, y no la dejará marchar, pero tal vez se pueda encontrar alguna esperanza. He aprendido que muchos de vosotros teméis la tormenta verde y la llamáis maldita. Me he enterado de que cuando la tormenta verde arremete, os cubrís la cabeza, cerráis las puertas, cerráis las ventanas y rezáis a los dioses de vuestros padres para que os liberen. No sé si esto es correcto.\n\nHe visto la tierra. He hablado con ella. He hablado con los que viven de la tierra y tratan de cultivarla o saben de esas cosas. Me dicen que hay vida en la tierra, cuando la tormenta ha pasado; vida que apenas existía antes de la tormenta. Nuestros ancianos hablan de días en los que el cielo estaba despejado y era azul como los vestidos de nuestras mujeres, y el Sol brillaba sobre nuestras cabezas.\n\nRezo para poder ver el cielo azul sobre las grandes ciudades antes de mi muerte. Rezo por ti, acechador de estas tierras, para que puedas verlo también. Que tengas paz."

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:676
    old "Trainee"
    new "Aprendiz"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:676
    old "She has made me really proud today. When her little sister was in danger, she showed resourcefulness, courage and skill. She moved and acted like a real Stalker, with strength, and focus, tempered with the grace of her youth. Her training is almost complete. All she lacks now is experience.\n\nSoon, she will have to face the trial of the Zone, and walk alone. As much as this fills me with pride, I cannot deny that I fear the perils she will face might take her away from me. But I am confident that she will walk the path that is set out for her. If I had not seen potential in her, I would not have initiated her to this dangerous life, but she is worthy.\n\nI believe in her. As for the little one, a punishment is in order.\n\n- Personal records, D 184, Y 416 since the Founding of Zeta"
    new "Hoy me ha hecho sentir muy orgulloso. Cuando su hermanita estaba en peligro, ha demostrado ingenio, valor y habilidad. Se ha movido y ha actuado como una verdadera Acechadora, con fuerza y concentración, templada con la gracia de su juventud. Su entrenamiento está casi completo. Lo único que le falta es la experiencia.\n\nPronto tendrá que enfrentarse a la prueba de la Zona, y caminar sola. Por mucho que esto me llene de orgullo, no puedo negar que temo que los peligros a los que se enfrentará la alejen de mí. Pero confío en que recorrerá el camino que se le ha trazado. Si no hubiera visto potencial en ella, no la habría iniciado en esta vida peligrosa, pero es digna.\n\nCreo en ella. En cuanto a la pequeña, se impone un castigo.\n\n- Registros personales, D 184, Y 416 desde la Fundación de Zeta"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:692
    old "Exploring the ruins both in the desert and around the city, and comparing them to the relatively new buildings of Zeta, I have come to the conclusion that the founders of the city may have built upon preexisting ruins, breathing new life in an ancient civilisation.\n\nI am unclear as to why they would have chosen such an antique model to build upon, rather than trying to piece together the ruins of the civilisation they were a part of themselves. Maybe this was easier. After all, little knowledge is needed to pile large blocks of stone one upon the other.\n\nI myself would not know how to start building the complex structures that I see crumbled in ruins in Old Cairo. Maybe that knowledge, that technology was lost, and they went for something that was more readily available.\n\n- Personal records, D 326, Y 429 since the Founding of Zeta"
    new "Explorando las ruinas tanto en el desierto como en los alrededores de la ciudad, y comparándolas con los edificios relativamente nuevos de Zeta, he llegado a la conclusión de que los fundadores de la ciudad pueden haber construido sobre ruinas preexistentes, insuflando nueva vida a una civilización antigua.\n\nNo tengo claro por qué habrían elegido un modelo tan antiguo para construir, en lugar de intentar reconstruir ellos mismos las ruinas de la civilización de la que formaban parte. Quizá esto fuera más fácil. Al fin y al cabo, se necesitan pocos conocimientos para apilar grandes bloques de piedra unos sobre otros.\n\nYo mismo no sabría cómo empezar a construir las complejas estructuras que veo desmoronadas en las ruinas del Viejo Cairo. Tal vez ese conocimiento, esa tecnología, se perdió, y optaron por algo que era más fácil de conseguir.\n\n- Registros personales, D 326, Y 429 desde la Fundación de Zeta"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:705
    old "Although I was educated in Zeta, many years of travel and exploration have made me something of an outsider, I guess that even those who survive crossing through a Zone, are forever changed nonetheless.\n\nOther Stalkers have found their residence in Zeta, others still prefer the lawless Raiders of Adira. I chose the middle path, and founded my House on the outskirts, outside of the confines of Zeta.\n\nI traded some of the protection that the walls of the city offer for a degree of freedom that I might otherwise not have. Hopefully, this will not come to damage my family.\n\n- Personal records, D 52, Y 430 since the Founding of Zeta"
    new "Aunque fui educado en Zeta, muchos años de viajes y exploración me han convertido en una especie de forastero, supongo que incluso los que sobreviven a la travesía de una Zona, quedan cambiados para siempre de todos modos.\n\nOtros Acechadores han encontrado su residencia en Zeta, otros siguen prefiriendo los Invasores sin ley de Adira. Yo elegí el camino del medio y fundé mi Casa en las afueras, fuera de los confines de Zeta.\n\nCambié parte de la protección que ofrecen las murallas de la ciudad por un grado de libertad que de otro modo no tendría. Espero que esto no llegue a perjudicar a mi familia.\n\n- Registros personales, D 52, Y 430 desde la Fundación de Zeta"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:717
    old "The laws of Zeta are few and upholding them beyond what the guards can do, falls on each of us who have the means and skills to do so.\n\nBetween the few written and spoken rules, a lot of posturing and an almost animalistic sense of personal boundaries, it is ultimately the sensible application of violence that regulates the balance of living in Zeta, under what passes for its laws.\n\nEven so, Zeta is a peaceful place, where people can thrive even when they renounce the way of violence.\n\nBy comparison Adira, or the badlands, the recesses of the desert and the Zone are a chaotic sinkhole of violence, prevarication, murder and abuse.\n\n- Personal records, D 116, Y 432 since the Founding of Zeta"
    new "Las leyes de Zeta son pocas y mantenerlas más allá de lo que puedan hacer los guardias, recae en cada uno de nosotros que tenga los medios y las habilidades para hacerlo.\n\nEntre las pocas reglas escritas y habladas, muchas posturas y un sentido casi animal de los límites personales, es en última instancia la aplicación sensata de la violencia lo que regula el equilibrio de la vida en Zeta, bajo lo que pasa por sus leyes. \n\nAún así, Zeta es un lugar pacífico, donde la gente puede prosperar incluso cuando renuncia al camino de la violencia.\n\nEn comparación, Adira, o las tierras malas, los recovecos del desierto y la Zona son un caótico sumidero de violencia, prevaricación, asesinato y abuso.\n\n- Registros personales, D 116, Y 432 desde la Fundación de Zeta"

    # game/scripts/codex_content.rpy:729
    old "My recent visits to the palace confirm my suspicion... there are a few buildings in Zeta that are thousands of years old.\n\nI think the newer ones have been modelled on those early structures. Are we just an echo of something our ancestors cobbled together from the ruins of what was left after the End of Days?\n\n- Personal records, D 109, Y 437 since the Founding of Zeta"
    new "Mis recientes visitas al palacio confirman mi sospecha... Hay algunos edificios en Zeta que tienen miles de años de antigüedad.\n\nCreo que los más nuevos han sido modelados a partir de esas primeras estructuras. ¿Somos sólo un eco de algo que nuestros antepasados improvisaron a partir de las ruinas de lo que quedó tras el Fin de los Días?\n\n- Registros personales, D 109, Y 437 desde la Fundación de Zeta"

